getting killed to do it.

226
00:18:28,066 --> 00:18:32,153
But I'm out.
I know exactly what I gotta do.

227
00:18:36,533 --> 00:18:38,952
<i>So you were scared,
weren't you, Goldie?</i>

228
00:18:39,035 --> 00:18:41,663
<i>Somebody wanted you dead
and you knew it.</i>

229
00:18:41,746 --> 00:18:44,499
<i>So you hit the saloons, the bad places,</i>

230
00:18:44,582 --> 00:18:48,878
<i>looking for the biggest,
meanest lug around and finding me.</i>

231
00:18:48,962 --> 00:18:51,631
<i>I'm gonna find
that son of a bitch that killed you,</i>

232
00:18:51,714 --> 00:18:54,592
<i>and I'm gonna give him the hard goodbye.</i>

233
00:18:55,927 --> 00:18:58,847
<i>Walk down
the right back alley in Sin City...</i>

234
00:18:58,930 --> 00:19:02,225
- Leave your hands off Nancy.
<i>- ...and you could find anything.</i>

235
00:19:02,308 --> 00:19:05,061
That coat looks like Baghdad.

236
00:19:05,145 --> 00:19:08,064
So does your face. Take off!

237
00:19:13,486 --> 00:19:16,489
He's new here, Marv.
He didn't know.

238
00:19:16,573 --> 00:19:19,075
<i>Kadie's is my kind of joint.</i>

239
00:19:20,577 --> 00:19:22,871
<i>Nancy's just getting
started with her gig,</i>

240
00:19:22,954 --> 00:19:26,207
<i>but already the crowd's
breathing hard.</i>

241
00:19:26,291 --> 00:19:28,501
<i>Plenty of nights
I've drooled over Nancy,</i>

242
00:19:28,585 --> 00:19:32,255
<i>shoulder to shoulder
with all the other losers like me.</i>

243
00:19:32,338 --> 00:19:35,925
<i>But that's not
what I'm lookin' for tonight.</i>

244
00:19:36,926 --> 00:19:38,303
What'll it be, Marv?

245
00:19:38,386 --> 00:19:41,264
A shot and a brew, Shellie,
and keep 'em comin'.

246
00:19:41,347 --> 00:19:45,101
Sure, honey.
You take it slow, now.

247
00:19:59,782 --> 00:20:02,869
<i>Most people think Marv is crazy.</i>

248
00:20:02,952 --> 00:20:06,372
<i>He just had the rotten luck
of being born in the wrong century.</i>

249
00:20:06,456 --> 00:20:09,167
<i>He'd be right at home
on some ancient battlefield,</i>

250
00:20:09,250 --> 00:20:11,628
<i>swinging an axe into somebody's face.</i>

251
00:20:12,128 --> 00:20:16,549
<i>Or in a Roman arena taking
a sword to other gladiators like him.</i>

252
00:20:16,633 --> 00:20:20,637
<i>They'd have tossed him girls
like Nancy back then.</i>

253
00:20:23,389 --> 00:20:26,184
Show's over, dickwad. Drink up.

254
00:20:26,267 --> 00:20:29,145
That's one fine-looking coat
you're wearing there.

255
00:20:32,148 --> 00:20:36,152
Your killin' days are over, you
over-the-hill, do-gooder son of a bitch.

256
00:20:36,945 --> 00:20:41,950
<i>I love hit men. No matter what
you do to them, you don't feel bad.</i>

257
00:20:49,958 --> 00:20:52,252
- Take it off.
- What?

258
00:20:52,335 --> 00:20:54,754
A fine coat,
you're bleeding all over it.

259
00:20:54,837 --> 00:20:57,340
All right, it's all yours.
Oh, God!

260
00:20:57,423 --> 00:21:01,135
It wasn't you losers who killed Goldie.

261
00:21:01,219 --> 00:21:05,682
The guy who did that,
he knew what he was doing.

262
00:21:06,808 --> 00:21:09,018
So tell me, man. Who sent you?

263
00:21:12,188 --> 00:21:14,274
I don't hear you giving me any names.

264
00:21:14,357 --> 00:21:18,069
So I guess when I shot you in the belly
I aimed a little too high.

265
00:21:21,030 --> 00:21:25,660
You keep holding out on me like this,
and I'm gonna have to get really nasty.

266
00:21:29,622 --> 00:21:34,377
It was Telly...
Telly Stern passed me the order.

267
00:21:35,420 --> 00:21:38,298
He runs the tables over
to the Triple Ace Club.

268
00:21:39,424 --> 00:21:41,801
Thanks again.

269
00:21:47,098 --> 00:21:48,975
<i>Then the damnedest thing happens.</i>

270
00:21:49,058 --> 00:21:53,313
<i>For a second, I smell the angel smell
that belonged to my Goldie.</i>

271
00:21:53,396 --> 00:21:55,732
<i>Just need my medicine, is all.</i>

272
00:21:55,815 --> 00:21:58,067
Bastard.

273
00:21:58,151 --> 00:22:01,404
You're gonna pay
for what you did to me.

274
00:22:04,240 --> 00:22:05,742
Feel like talking, Louie?

275
00:22:05,825 --> 00:22:08,328
How many got paid off
for the frame, Louie?

276
00:22:08,411 --> 00:22:10,163
How many for the kill?

277
00:22:10,246 --> 00:22:12,832
It was Connelly.
He set me up.

278
00:22:15,418 --> 00:22:17,420
He'll never talk.

279
00:22:20,423 --> 00:22:23,593
I don't know about you,
but I'm havin' a ball.

280
00:22:24,886 --> 00:22:28,806
<i>Connelly talks. They all talk.</i>

281
00:22:29,724 --> 00:22:31,976
And what have been
your sins, my son?

282
00:22:32,060 --> 00:22:34,645
Well, Padre,
I don't want to keep you up all night,

283
00:22:34,729 --> 00:22:37,774
so I'll just fill you in
on the latest batch.

284
00:22:37,857 --> 00:22:40,860
These here hands of mine,
they got blood all over 'em.

285
00:22:40,943 --> 00:22:43,029
You're speaking figuratively.

286
00:22:43,112 --> 00:22:47,700
When I need to find something out,
I just go out and look for somebody

287
00:22:47,784 --> 00:22:50,286
that knows more than me,
and I go and I ask them.

288
00:22:50,369 --> 00:22:53,539
Sometimes, I ask pretty hard.

289
00:22:53,623 --> 00:22:59,545
By way of a "for instance,"
I killed three men tonight.

290
00:22:59,629 --> 00:23:01,005
Tortured 'em first.

291
00:23:01,089 --> 00:23:05,384
You might say I been
working my way up the food chain.

292
00:23:05,468 --> 00:23:08,346
First two were minnows,
small-time messengers.

293
00:23:08,429 --> 00:23:13,267
But it was Connelly, the money man,
who fingered you, Padre.

294
00:23:13,351 --> 00:23:16,020
Dear Lord, man,
this is a house of God.

295
00:23:16,104 --> 00:23:19,899
Just give me a damn name.

296
00:23:19,982 --> 00:23:23,319
- Roark.
- You really are pushing your luck,

297
00:23:23,402 --> 00:23:26,322
feeding me garbage like that.

298
00:23:26,405 --> 00:23:27,573
It can't be that big.

299
00:23:27,657 --> 00:23:29,992
There's a farm
at North Cross and Lennox.

300
00:23:30,076 --> 00:23:32,995
It's all there.
Find out for yourself.

301
00:23:33,079 --> 00:23:34,497
And while you're at it,

302
00:23:34,580 --> 00:23:40,503
ask yourself if that corpse of a slut
is worth dying for.

303
00:23:40,920 --> 00:23:42,964
<i>Worth dying for.</i>

304
00:23:43,047 --> 00:23:45,091
<i>Worth killing for.</i>

305
00:23:45,174 --> 00:23:47,510
<i>Worth going to hell for.</i>

306
00:23:47,593 --> 00:23:49,512
Amen.

307
00:23:53,015 --> 00:23:55,893
<i>His keys say the padre drove a Mercedes,</i>

308
00:23:55,977 --> 00:23:59,605
<i>or at least that's what they're
passing off as a Mercedes these days.</i>

309
00:23:59,689 --> 00:24:03,693
<i>Modern cars:
they all look like electric shavers.</i>

310
00:24:10,449 --> 00:24:12,076
Goldie.

311
00:24:14,787 --> 00:24:16,038
Goldie!

312
00:24:26,799 --> 00:24:28,968
It couldn't be Goldie.

313
00:24:29,051 --> 00:24:33,222
<i>It's my own fault, and nobody else's,
that I got confused.</i>

314
00:24:33,306 --> 00:24:37,185
<i>I've been having so much fun
I forgot to take my medicine.</i>

315
00:24:37,268 --> 00:24:39,187
<i>That wasn't Goldie back there.</i>

316
00:24:39,270 --> 00:24:40,688
<i>Goldie's dead,</i>

317
00:24:40,771 --> 00:24:44,734
<i>and that's the whole reason that
I've been doing what I've been doing.</i>

318
00:24:44,817 --> 00:24:48,613
<i>When you got a condition,
it's bad to forget your medicine.</i>

319
00:24:51,240 --> 00:24:52,825
<i>The cold thing,</i>

320
00:24:52,909 --> 00:24:56,746
<i>it creeps into my gut and tells me
one more time it won't let go.</i>

321
00:24:56,829 --> 00:25:00,416
<i>This is a bad place, this farm.</i>

322
00:25:00,499 --> 00:25:02,084
<i>People have died here...</i>

323
00:25:03,878 --> 00:25:05,463
<i>...the wrong way.</i>

324
00:25:08,424 --> 00:25:10,426
I don't want to fight, pooch.

325
00:25:13,930 --> 00:25:16,015
I got no gripe with you.

326
00:25:18,434 --> 00:25:19,602
Easy, boy.

327
00:25:23,439 --> 00:25:26,359
<i>No way I was gonna use
my gun on you, buddy.</i>

328
00:25:26,442 --> 00:25:29,153
<i>It's whoever owns you
I'm curious about,</i>

329
00:25:29,237 --> 00:25:33,032
<i>because there's blood on your breath,
and I think I know what kind.</i>

330
00:25:33,115 --> 00:25:35,868
<i>So I sniff around to see what's buried.</i>

331
00:25:39,789 --> 00:25:41,249
<i>Here we go.</i>

332
00:25:46,796 --> 00:25:49,882
<i>It's impossible.
Nobody can sneak up on me.</i>

333
00:25:55,346 --> 00:26:00,559
<i>I go blind.
Not a sound. Nobody's that quiet.</i>

334
00:26:00,643 --> 00:26:03,854
<i>Except the one who snuck
into that hotel room two nights ago.</i>

335
00:26:03,938 --> 00:26:07,900
It was you, you bastard.
You killed her.

336
00:26:07,984 --> 00:26:10,528
You killed Goldie.

337
00:26:10,611 --> 00:26:12,280
It was...

338
00:26:13,823 --> 00:26:15,408
<i>I blew it, Goldie.</i>

339
00:26:16,033 --> 00:26:18,577
<i>I found your killer,
but he was better than me.</i>

340
00:26:19,161 --> 00:26:21,205
<i>Too quiet, too quick.</i>

341
00:26:21,289 --> 00:26:23,749
<i>A killer born.</i>

342
00:26:23,833 --> 00:26:26,335
<i>Why didn't he finish the job?</i>

343
00:26:39,348 --> 00:26:43,102
He keeps the heads.
He eats the rest.

344
00:26:43,185 --> 00:26:46,522
- Lucille?
- It's not just that wolf of his.

345
00:26:48,274 --> 00:26:51,444
The wolf just gets scraps.

346
00:26:51,527 --> 00:26:53,487
Bones.

347
00:26:53,571 --> 00:26:55,906
It's him.

348
00:26:55,990 --> 00:27:00,453
He... eats... people.

349
00:27:01,454 --> 00:27:04,957
- He cooks them like they were steaks.
- Let's get you warm.

350
00:27:05,041 --> 00:27:07,293
Just like they were steaks.

351
00:27:07,376 --> 00:27:09,712
Now he's got both of us.

352
00:27:09,795 --> 00:27:12,923
It's all right.
Take a nice, slow breath.

353
00:27:13,799 --> 00:27:16,635
Just look at the heads on the wall.

354
00:27:16,719 --> 00:27:18,888
The heads on the wall.

355
00:27:19,513 --> 00:27:21,432
The heads on the wall.

356
00:27:21,515 --> 00:27:25,519
Son of a bitch!
He kept smiling that damned smile.

357
00:27:25,603 --> 00:27:29,648
He made me watch him
suck the meat off my fingers.

358
00:27:29,732 --> 00:27:32,526
- He made me watch!
- Oh, Jesus.

359
00:27:32,610 --> 00:27:37,490
He made me watch!

360
00:27:45,081 --> 00:27:47,416
Christ, I could use a cigarette.

361
00:27:48,167 --> 00:27:52,004
<i>Dames. Sometimes all they
gotta do is let it out.</i>

362
00:27:52,088 --> 00:27:55,299
<i>And a few buckets later,
there's no way you'd know.</i>

363
00:27:55,383 --> 00:27:58,135
You've brought us
some big trouble this time, Marv.

364
00:27:58,219 --> 00:28:02,890
Whoever's behind this whole thing has
his connections right in the department.

365
00:28:02,973 --> 00:28:05,184
Any leads?

366
00:28:05,267 --> 00:28:08,854
One guy I talked to told me
it was Roark running the show.

367
00:28:08,938 --> 00:28:13,901
Whoever it is, he knew I was checking
out that hooker almost before I did.

368
00:28:13,984 --> 00:28:17,613
- What hooker?
- The one you've been obsessing over.

369
00:28:17,696 --> 00:28:19,824
The dead one.

370
00:28:19,907 --> 00:28:22,076
Goldie.

371
00:28:22,159 --> 00:28:24,620
I didn't know she was a hooker.

372
00:28:24,703 --> 00:28:27,873
Doesn't make any difference
about anything.

373
00:28:29,834 --> 00:28:34,296
- But I didn't know that.
- She was high-class stuff.

374
00:28:34,380 --> 00:28:36,173
Must have shown you quite a time.

375
00:28:36,257 --> 00:28:38,426
Quiet. There's a car coming.

376
00:28:42,304 --> 00:28:44,765
Kevin!

377
00:28:45,933 --> 00:28:49,728
<i>All I've got is a face... and a name.</i>

378
00:28:49,812 --> 00:28:51,814
I'll see you later, Kevin.

379
00:29:01,782 --> 00:29:02,825
Let's go.

380
00:29:19,633 --> 00:29:21,427
They're done checking the house.

381
00:29:21,510 --> 00:29:23,554
They're coming this way.

382
00:29:23,637 --> 00:29:26,724
Bastards. I'll show them.

383
00:29:31,812 --> 00:29:35,900
You're not gonna get
either of us killed, Marv.

384
00:29:35,983 --> 00:29:38,694
No, don't shoot! Please.

385
00:29:38,777 --> 00:29:41,030
Listen to me.
I'm his parole officer.

386
00:29:41,113 --> 00:29:43,574
He's unconscious and unarmed,

387
00:29:43,657 --> 00:29:46,660
so there's no need to kill him.

388
00:29:52,750 --> 00:29:55,127
Captain, the target,
there's no sign of him.

389
00:29:55,211 --> 00:29:56,462
Here's a sign!

390
00:30:11,227 --> 00:30:14,939
That there is one
damn fine coat you're wearing.

391
00:30:22,571 --> 00:30:26,158
<i>I keep coming back to that cop
I just killed and what he told me.</i>

392
00:30:26,242 --> 00:30:29,036
<i>I was pretty steamed about
what he'd done to Lucille,</i>

393
00:30:29,119 --> 00:30:31,664
<i>so I took my time
with that son of a bitch.</i>

394
00:30:31,747 --> 00:30:36,001
<i>It wasn't till I showed him all those
pieces of himself that he said it.</i>

395
00:30:36,085 --> 00:30:41,757
<i>Just a name:
Patrick Henry Roark, man of the cloth.</i>

396
00:30:41,840 --> 00:30:44,927
<i>Could've become president,
but he chose to serve God.</i>

397
00:30:45,010 --> 00:30:49,515
<i>Along the way, he happened to become
the most powerful man in the state.</i>

398
00:30:49,598 --> 00:30:53,435
<i>He's brought down mayors and governors
like they were nothing.</i>

399
00:30:53,519 --> 00:30:57,189
<i>He even made his rotten brother
a US senator without breaking a sweat.</i>

400
00:30:57,273 --> 00:31:01,151
<i>And here he's gonna get killed
in the name of a dead hooker.</i>

401
00:31:02,778 --> 00:31:07,408
<i>I'm getting used to the idea. More
and more, I'm liking the sound of it.</i>

402
00:31:08,951 --> 00:31:12,579
<i>Then it hits me like a kick in the nuts.</i>

403
00:31:12,663 --> 00:31:14,540
<i>What if I'm wrong?</i>

404
00:31:14,623 --> 00:31:16,375
<i>I've got a condition.</i>

405
00:31:16,458 --> 00:31:18,711
<i>I get confused sometimes.</i>

406
00:31:18,794 --> 00:31:22,631
<i>And with Lucille dead,
I can't get my medicine.</i>

407
00:31:22,715 --> 00:31:24,967
<i>What if I've imagined all of this?</i>

408
00:31:25,050 --> 00:31:30,347
<i>What if I've turned into what they've
always said I was gonna turn into?</i>

409
00:31:30,431 --> 00:31:32,808
<i>A maniac.</i>

410
00:31:32,891 --> 00:31:35,227
<i>A psycho killer.</i>

411
00:31:35,311 --> 00:31:38,480
<i>Can't kill a man
without knowing for sure you ought to.</i>

412
00:31:38,564 --> 00:31:40,607
<i>I've gotta know for sure.</i>

413
00:31:43,652 --> 00:31:48,157
<i>The merchandise is on display
by the time I make my way to Old Town.</i>

414
00:31:48,240 --> 00:31:50,951
<i>For an hour or so,
I ask around about Goldie.</i>

415
00:31:51,035 --> 00:31:53,829
<i>I don't get any answers,
but I know I'm bound to.</i>

416
00:31:53,912 --> 00:31:56,040
<i>Lucille said Goldie was a hooker,</i>

417
00:31:56,123 --> 00:31:58,917
<i>and if she was, she has roots here:</i>

418
00:31:59,001 --> 00:32:01,795
<i>Friends, maybe even family.</i>

419
00:32:06,508 --> 00:32:09,595
You can't be Goldie.
Goldie's dead.

420
00:32:20,689 --> 00:32:23,984
Goldie. Yeah, sure, right.

421
00:32:24,068 --> 00:32:28,113
I haven't eaten anything
or taken my medicine for days now.

422
00:32:28,197 --> 00:32:30,783
No wonder I'm seeing things.

423
00:32:30,866 --> 00:32:32,326
Bastard!

424
00:32:38,040 --> 00:32:39,958
He's crazy.

425
00:32:40,042 --> 00:32:43,087
Hit him again, Wendy. Harder.

426
00:32:44,713 --> 00:32:47,132
Wait a minute.
Why did she call you Wendy?

427
00:32:47,216 --> 00:32:49,551
Because that's my name, you ape.

428
00:32:50,135 --> 00:32:54,515
Goldie was my sister.
My twin sister.

429
00:32:54,598 --> 00:32:56,975
I guess she was the nice one.

430
00:33:03,232 --> 00:33:06,819
Goldie and the other six,
where are they?

431
00:33:06,902 --> 00:33:08,987
What did you do to them?

432
00:33:09,071 --> 00:33:11,490
You crazy goddamn broad.

433
00:33:11,573 --> 00:33:13,492
Just take a look at this mug.

434
00:33:13,575 --> 00:33:17,788
Would any of you dames let me get
close enough to you to kill you?

435
00:33:17,871 --> 00:33:21,500
None of you would, but Goldie.

436
00:33:21,583 --> 00:33:24,795
And she only did because
she thought I could protect her.

437
00:33:24,878 --> 00:33:30,092
And I'll bet those cops didn't do a damn
thing about those other girls, did they?

438
00:33:30,175 --> 00:33:35,180
But as soon as they had me for a fall
guy, they showed up, guns blazing.

439
00:33:35,264 --> 00:33:40,769
But they didn't get me, and I've been
killing my way to the truth ever since.

440
00:33:40,853 --> 00:33:44,523
So, go ahead, doll.

441
00:33:44,606 --> 00:33:49,236
Shoot me now,
or get the hell out of my way.

442
00:33:56,034 --> 00:33:58,203
Nuts.

443
00:33:58,287 --> 00:34:01,790
OK, I'm glad we got
all that sorted out.

444
00:34:03,459 --> 00:34:05,961
- What the hell?
- I tied those knots!

445
00:34:06,044 --> 00:34:09,631
- That's my specialty!
- You sat there and took it,

446
00:34:09,715 --> 00:34:12,885
when you could've taken my gun away
any time you wanted to.

447
00:34:12,968 --> 00:34:17,347
Well, sure. I thought I might be able
to talk some sense into you.

448
00:34:17,431 --> 00:34:20,809
And I probably would have had
to paste you one,

449
00:34:20,893 --> 00:34:22,811
and I don't hurt girls.

450
00:34:22,895 --> 00:34:25,230
I need a pair of handcuffs.

451
00:34:25,314 --> 00:34:28,400
What style do you want?
I got a collection.

452
00:34:28,484 --> 00:34:32,362
Just give him the ones
you got with you, Gail.

453
00:34:32,446 --> 00:34:35,407
It was a farm boy named Kevin
who killed Goldie,

454
00:34:35,491 --> 00:34:38,827
but it was Cardinal Roark
who was behind it, and I don't know why.

455
00:34:38,911 --> 00:34:41,371
I know that sounds crazy.

456
00:34:41,455 --> 00:34:44,750
No, it doesn't.
Goldie worked the clergy.

457
00:34:44,833 --> 00:34:49,087
<i>Just like that, a whopper of
a puzzle piece falls smack in my lap.</i>

458
00:34:49,171 --> 00:34:51,840
<i>I'm too dumb to put
the whole picture together yet,</i>

459
00:34:51,924 --> 00:34:55,219
<i>but she fires up two cigarettes
and hands me one,</i>

460
00:34:55,302 --> 00:34:56,887
<i>and I taste her lipstick on it.</i>

461
00:34:56,970 --> 00:35:01,600
<i>And suddenly, my heart's pounding
so loud I can't hear anything else.</i>

462
00:35:01,683 --> 00:35:06,271
