464
00:35:08,565 --> 00:35:10,567
Yeah, yeah. This'll do.

465
00:35:10,651 --> 00:35:16,156
I'm gonna be needing a dozen two-foot
lengths of this rubber tubing...

466
00:35:17,241 --> 00:35:19,618
...and a spool of razor wire...

467
00:35:20,744 --> 00:35:24,790
...and a pair of those special gloves
that'll let me handle the wire.

468
00:35:24,873 --> 00:35:27,960
Beefing up
the old home security, huh?

469
00:35:28,043 --> 00:35:29,461
You can bet your ass.

470
00:35:29,545 --> 00:35:33,799
She was my sister,
so I'm in this one to the end.

471
00:35:33,882 --> 00:35:37,553
Why are you willing to go up against
Roark for someone you barely knew?

472
00:35:37,636 --> 00:35:42,724
She was nice to me, gave me
something I didn't even know existed.

473
00:35:42,808 --> 00:35:47,354
I wasn't never even able to buy a woman.

474
00:35:47,437 --> 00:35:50,232
You know, the way I look.

475
00:35:50,983 --> 00:35:54,820
<i>I take my mind off her
and I crawl back inside myself.</i>

476
00:35:54,903 --> 00:35:57,864
<i>It's almost killing time,
and I'd better get sharp.</i>

477
00:35:57,948 --> 00:36:02,160
<i>I check the list:
rubber tubing, gas, saw,</i>

478
00:36:02,244 --> 00:36:06,290
<i>gloves, cuffs, razor wire, hatchet,</i>

479
00:36:06,373 --> 00:36:08,625
<i>Gladys and my mitts.</i>

480
00:36:08,709 --> 00:36:12,629
- We're close enough. Pull over.
- Yes, Marv.

481
00:36:13,880 --> 00:36:15,299
Keep the engine runnin'.

482
00:36:15,382 --> 00:36:20,137
If I'm not back in 20 minutes, you get
the hell outta here and don't look back.

483
00:36:20,220 --> 00:36:22,139
Kill him for me, Marv.

484
00:36:24,099 --> 00:36:26,310
Kill him good.

485
00:36:26,393 --> 00:36:28,145
