532
00:40:06,738 --> 00:40:08,615
<i>I owe you, Goldie.</i>

533
00:40:08,698 --> 00:40:11,076
<i>I owe you one and I'm gonna pay up.</i>

534
00:40:11,159 --> 00:40:14,162
<i>So, if going after Roark
means dying, win or lose,</i>

535
00:40:14,246 --> 00:40:18,750
<i>hell, I'll die laughing if I know
I've done this one thing right.</i>

536
00:40:23,421 --> 00:40:25,966
Quiet as a grave out here.
No sign of target.

537
00:40:26,049 --> 00:40:27,509
<i>All right, keep a lookout.</i>

538
00:40:44,693 --> 00:40:47,988
- Kevin?
- What's left of him, anyways.

539
00:40:49,698 --> 00:40:51,283
The dog ate the rest.

540
00:40:58,999 --> 00:41:03,211
Oh, my God. You monster.

541
00:41:03,295 --> 00:41:06,047
You demon.

542
00:41:06,131 --> 00:41:08,591
Don't scream or I'll plug you.

543
00:41:08,675 --> 00:41:12,304
He had the voice of an angel,

544
00:41:12,387 --> 00:41:14,806
yet he spoke only to me.

545
00:41:14,889 --> 00:41:18,810
And he's dead now
because of one stupid whore.

546
00:41:18,893 --> 00:41:21,855
