908
01:05:28,842 --> 01:05:32,846
They won't be watching the roads. Not
yet, they won't! Get me a damn hardtop!

909
01:05:32,929 --> 01:05:35,181
If I don't make it,
you can have your war.

910
01:05:35,265 --> 01:05:37,893
Get that gun out of my face now!

911
01:05:40,520 --> 01:05:42,314
Bastard!

912
01:05:47,027 --> 01:05:49,237
I forgot how quick you are.

913
01:05:51,239 --> 01:05:52,908
<i>My warrior woman.</i>

914
01:05:52,991 --> 01:05:55,619
<i>She almost yanks my head clean off</i>

915
01:05:55,702 --> 01:05:58,997
<i>shoving my mouth into hers
so hard it hurts.</i>

916
01:05:59,080 --> 01:06:02,542
<i>An explosion that blasts away
the dull, grey years</i>

917
01:06:02,626 --> 01:06:06,922
<i>between the now and that one fiery night
when she was mine.</i>

918
01:06:07,797 --> 01:06:10,592
A hardtop with a decent engine.

919
01:06:10,675 --> 01:06:13,053
And make sure it's got a big trunk.

920
01:06:15,096 --> 01:06:18,266
I'll always love you, baby.

921
01:06:18,350 --> 01:06:22,228
Always... and never.

922
01:06:30,236 --> 01:06:32,197
Where'd you find that heap?

923
01:06:32,280 --> 01:06:35,909
Just look at that trunk.
We'll never fit 'em all in.

924
01:06:35,992 --> 01:06:39,537
Gail? Unless there's something else
you want me to do,

925
01:06:39,621 --> 01:06:41,581
you think maybe I could go home?

926
01:06:41,665 --> 01:06:45,835
All this blood and stuff's got me
feeling like maybe I'm gonna hurl.

927
01:06:45,919 --> 01:06:48,088
Sure, Becky, go home.

928
01:06:48,171 --> 01:06:50,966
But don't you talk to anybody,
not even your mom.

929
01:06:51,049 --> 01:06:53,927
They'll never fit in that trunk.

930
01:06:54,010 --> 01:06:57,806
Not like this, they won't. Miho.

931
01:06:58,223 --> 01:07:00,183
Dry your hair as soon as you get home!

932
01:07:00,266 --> 01:07:02,519
You'll catch cold if you don't.

933
01:07:14,280 --> 01:07:16,700
Hey, Becky. Gail said no calls.

934
01:07:16,783 --> 01:07:20,704
I just want to hear my mom's voice.
I won't tell her nothing.

935
01:07:20,787 --> 01:07:23,415
Please, don't say nothing to Gail.

936
01:07:25,917 --> 01:07:27,502
Hey, Mom?

937
01:07:31,172 --> 01:07:33,883
<i>Dizzy dames. What were they thinking,</i>

938
01:07:33,967 --> 01:07:37,095
<i>sticking me with a beat-up bucket
of bolts like this?</i>

939
01:07:37,178 --> 01:07:39,931
<i>We were barely able to get
the trunk closed as it was,</i>

940
01:07:40,014 --> 01:07:41,641
<i>we packed it so tight.</i>

941
01:07:41,725 --> 01:07:46,604
<i>There wasn't anything we could do
but pile Jackie Bo yin right next to me,</i>

942
01:07:46,688 --> 01:07:50,608
<i>out where anybody
who cares to look will see him.</i>

943
01:07:51,818 --> 01:07:55,739
<i>Go ahead, take one of his cigarettes.</i>

944
01:07:56,698 --> 01:07:58,575
<i>It'll help.</i>

945
01:08:23,016 --> 01:08:27,353
It's got you smoking there, bud.

946
01:08:31,941 --> 01:08:35,153
You shut the hell up, Jackie Boy.

947
01:08:35,236 --> 01:08:37,363
You're dead.

948
01:08:37,447 --> 01:08:41,659
I'm just imagining this,
so shut the hell up.

949
01:08:41,743 --> 01:08:46,664
Well, it tells you something
about your state of mind, don't it?

950
01:08:46,748 --> 01:08:51,211
It's got you hearing things.
It's got your nerves shot.

951
01:08:52,504 --> 01:08:54,839
It's got you smoking.

952
01:08:54,923 --> 01:08:58,927
You know it's true.

953
01:08:59,010 --> 01:09:02,764
Nobody ever really quits.

954
01:09:04,307 --> 01:09:09,062
A smoker's a smoker
when the chips are down.

955
01:09:09,145 --> 01:09:14,067
- And your chips are down.
- I'm fine. You shut the hell up.

956
01:09:15,443 --> 01:09:18,112
Will you look at that?

957
01:09:19,614 --> 01:09:23,117
Those hookers let you down.

958
01:09:24,410 --> 01:09:29,541
What are you gonna do
when you run outta gas, call AAA?

959
01:09:29,624 --> 01:09:33,878
You sucker for the babes, you.

960
01:09:33,962 --> 01:09:36,881
You ain't even
gonna make it to the pits.

961
01:09:36,965 --> 01:09:40,134
You shut the hell up. I'll make it.

962
01:09:40,218 --> 01:09:43,555
Not unless you keep
your eyes on the road, sugar pie.

963
01:09:43,638 --> 01:09:45,306
Watch it!

964
01:09:48,226 --> 01:09:50,228
This is great.

965
01:09:50,311 --> 01:09:53,690
Just like being in a buddy movie.

966
01:09:53,773 --> 01:09:56,150
Shut up!

967
01:10:00,655 --> 01:10:03,241
Boy, you're screwed.

968
01:10:03,324 --> 01:10:05,368
It's over.

969
01:10:05,451 --> 01:10:07,954
You're flushed.

970
01:10:08,037 --> 01:10:10,915
This time, I can't bring myself
to tell him to shut up.

971
01:10:10,999 --> 01:10:15,044
Sure, he's an asshole.

972
01:10:15,128 --> 01:10:17,755
Sure, he's dead.

973
01:10:17,839 --> 01:10:21,426
Sure, I'm just imagining
that he's talking.

974
01:10:21,509 --> 01:10:25,597
None of that stops the bastard
from being absolutely right.

975
01:10:25,680 --> 01:10:29,100
I don't have a chance in hell
of outrunning this cop.

976
01:10:29,183 --> 01:10:31,436
Not in this heap.

977
01:10:31,519 --> 01:10:34,022
Pull over!

978
01:10:35,523 --> 01:10:38,902
The only question left
is whether I'm gonna kill him or not.

979
01:10:39,152 --> 01:10:41,613
Tough call.

980
01:10:41,696 --> 01:10:44,866
For all I know,
he's an honest cop, regular guy,

981
01:10:44,949 --> 01:10:49,120
a working stiff with a mortgage,
a wife and a pile of kids.

982
01:10:49,203 --> 01:10:51,497
My hand moves all on its own,

983
01:10:51,581 --> 01:10:55,627
sliding one of my guns to my lap
and thumbing back the hammer.

984
01:10:57,795 --> 01:11:02,800
- I don't know what to do.
- Better stop. You're making him mad.

985
01:11:04,177 --> 01:11:07,055
Whatever you say.

986
01:11:14,062 --> 01:11:17,732
Your friend here...
party a little too hard tonight?

987
01:11:19,275 --> 01:11:22,028
I'm the designated driver.

988
01:11:27,742 --> 01:11:30,954
Well, you're driving
with a busted tail light.

989
01:11:36,250 --> 01:11:38,378
I'll let you off with a warning.

990
01:11:46,135 --> 01:11:47,553
What next?

991
01:11:51,849 --> 01:11:56,562
<i>The tank goes dry
a quarter mile from the pits.</i>

992
01:11:56,646 --> 01:11:59,691
<i>I shove the T-Bird the rest of the way.</i>

993
01:11:59,774 --> 01:12:03,069
<i>A few minutes' more work
and it'll all be over.</i>

994
01:12:03,152 --> 01:12:06,531
<i>Jackie Boy
will go into the damn tar pits,</i>

995
01:12:06,614 --> 01:12:10,827
<i>I'll catch a train out of Sacred Oaks,
go home and call it a...</i>

996
01:12:22,130 --> 01:12:24,382
No more questions, Dallas.
Do what I say.

997
01:12:24,465 --> 01:12:28,177
Clear the streets.
We're in lockdown.

998
01:12:28,261 --> 01:12:30,888
We're not selling any tail in Old Town.

999
01:12:30,972 --> 01:12:33,349
Not tonight.

1000
01:12:36,769 --> 01:12:40,356
Don't struggle.
You'll only hurt yourself.

1001
01:12:40,440 --> 01:12:42,692
Your cause is lost.

1002
01:12:42,775 --> 01:12:44,360
We know everything.

1003
01:12:44,444 --> 01:12:48,656
Soon the corpse of Detective Rafferty
will be in our possession,

1004
01:12:48,740 --> 01:12:53,745
and the truce between your prostitutes
and the police will be shattered.

1005
01:12:53,828 --> 01:12:56,956
There'll be arrests.
There'll be deaths.

1006
01:12:57,040 --> 01:13:01,085
My employer will seize
what remains of this neighbourhood.

1007
01:13:01,169 --> 01:13:05,423
You will all be slaves.
Nothing can stop this.

1008
01:13:05,506 --> 01:13:10,553
But it is within your power
to save many lives

1009
01:13:10,636 --> 01:13:15,266
by facilitating
the process of transition,

1010
01:13:15,349 --> 01:13:20,897
by negotiating the terms
of the surrender of Old Town.

1011
01:13:20,980 --> 01:13:23,566
Son of a bitch! I know you.

1012
01:13:23,649 --> 01:13:28,780
I have suffered your kind before,
the dregs of Sin City.

1013
01:13:28,863 --> 01:13:30,865
I serve a new master now,

1014
01:13:30,948 --> 01:13:35,787
and soon you and all your wretched kind
will serve him as well.

1015
01:13:35,870 --> 01:13:41,292
Now, get dressed and shed a tear
for Dwight McCarthy if you must,

1016
01:13:41,375 --> 01:13:44,921
because, by now, he is surely dead.

1017
01:13:45,004 --> 01:13:47,757
You don't know him.

1018
01:13:47,840 --> 01:13:51,094
My man will find a way.

1019
01:13:51,177 --> 01:13:54,222
He always finds a way.

1020
01:13:55,223 --> 01:13:57,725
I can't fathom
these Americans always whining

1021
01:13:57,809 --> 01:14:01,312
and going on about
how they got it so bad.

1022
01:14:01,395 --> 01:14:03,648
This is a fine, grand country.

1023
01:14:03,731 --> 01:14:05,983
Guiding light
of the modern world, it is.

1024
01:14:06,067 --> 01:14:09,112
Low taxes, land of opportunity.

1025
01:14:09,195 --> 01:14:13,116
Where else would one bullet buy us
the fortune that we're getting for this?

1026
01:14:13,199 --> 01:14:16,119
Beats the hell
out of blowing up airports and churches

1027
01:14:16,202 --> 01:14:18,246
without shite to show for it.

1028
01:14:23,251 --> 01:14:28,172
- You find something, Murphy?
- Looks to be a poor, dead cop's badge.

1029
01:14:28,256 --> 01:14:30,299
It's all bent up.

1030
01:14:30,383 --> 01:14:33,177
What's this stuck in it?

1031
01:14:33,261 --> 01:14:35,263
Bloody hell. It's the bullet.

1032
01:14:44,564 --> 01:14:48,234
You son of a bitch! Bastard!

1033
01:14:49,610 --> 01:14:51,863
<i>They weren't cops, these four.</i>

1034
01:14:51,946 --> 01:14:53,698
<i>They were mercenaries.</i>

1035
01:14:53,781 --> 01:14:56,159
<i>If they were hired
by who I think they were,</i>

1036
01:14:56,242 --> 01:14:59,203
<i>the bad times
haven't even started yet.</i>

1037
01:14:59,287 --> 01:15:02,665
<i>And everything seemed
to be going so well.</i>

1038
01:15:14,844 --> 01:15:20,057
Remember, we don't have to deliver
every last inch of the man, Brian.

1039
01:15:20,141 --> 01:15:24,020
You got a good point there, Ronnie.
Lend me your knife.

1040
01:15:25,813 --> 01:15:28,900
Should I take a nap
while I'm doing all this waiting?

1041
01:15:28,983 --> 01:15:31,903
I'm at the bone, all right?

1042
01:15:34,238 --> 01:15:36,365
There we go.

1043
01:15:39,202 --> 01:15:43,331
Have you ever seen anything so pretty
in your whole life?

1044
01:15:44,415 --> 01:15:48,044
We'll be back for the three of you,
and if anyone happens by,

1045
01:15:48,127 --> 01:15:51,005
use your imagination, OK?

1046
01:16:00,932 --> 01:16:03,267
<i>Silence, now.</i>

1047
01:16:03,351 --> 01:16:05,728
<i>No air to breathe.</i>

1048
01:16:05,811 --> 01:16:09,857
<i>Only the horrid, oily tar taste
creeping up my nostrils.</i>

1049
01:16:11,150 --> 01:16:15,446
<i>Let it in. Let it fill your lungs.</i>

1050
01:16:15,529 --> 01:16:19,200
<i>They were counting on you
and you blew it.</i>

1051
01:16:20,159 --> 01:16:24,455
<i>Skinny, steely fingers at my wrist.</i>

1052
01:16:24,538 --> 01:16:28,251
<i>Miho, you're an angel.</i>

1053
01:16:28,334 --> 01:16:30,211
<i>You're a saint.</i>

1054
01:16:30,294 --> 01:16:32,505
<i>You're Mother Teresa.</i>

1055
01:16:32,588 --> 01:16:34,632
<i>You're Elvis.</i>

1056
01:16:34,715 --> 01:16:36,759
<i>You're God.</i>

1057
01:16:37,677 --> 01:16:42,974
<i>If you'd shown up ten minutes earlier,
we'd still have Jackie Boy's head.</i>

1058
01:16:43,057 --> 01:16:46,727
Dwight, they got Gail!

1059
01:16:47,603 --> 01:16:50,773
It's a cinch.
You got yourselves a spy in Old Town.

1060
01:16:50,856 --> 01:16:53,693
A stoolie who sold you out to the mob.

1061
01:16:53,776 --> 01:16:56,195
We gotta find out who it is
and rescue Gail.

1062
01:16:56,279 --> 01:16:58,322
First, we gotta get
Jackie Boy's head

1063
01:16:58,406 --> 01:17:02,618
before it gets to wherever it's going
and this situation blows wide open.

1064
01:17:02,702 --> 01:17:07,999
Miho, I hope to hell you left
one of 'em alive enough to talk.

1065
01:17:16,007 --> 01:17:19,176
<i>I let him know I'm not fooling around.</i>

1066
01:17:23,931 --> 01:17:26,017
<i>We talk.</i>

1067
01:17:35,026 --> 01:17:38,821
<i>Stay smart. Stay cool.</i>

1068
01:17:38,904 --> 01:17:42,366
<i>It's time to prove to your friends
that you're worth a damn.</i>

1069
01:17:42,450 --> 01:17:45,578
<i>Sometimes, that means dying.</i>

1070
01:17:45,661 --> 01:17:49,165
<i>Sometimes, it means killing
a whole lot of people.</i>

1071
01:17:49,248 --> 01:17:51,625
There they are.
What do we do?

1072
01:17:51,709 --> 01:17:53,961
We stop 'em, Dallas.

1073
01:18:02,303 --> 01:18:04,472
<i>Jackie Boy's head is so close to me</i>

1074
01:18:04,555 --> 01:18:08,392
<i>I could almost reach out
and grab it right then and there.</i>

1075
01:18:13,647 --> 01:18:15,733
Get the head! Get the head!

1076
01:18:17,485 --> 01:18:19,403
I got it! I got it!

1077
01:18:26,243 --> 01:18:28,871
Suck on this, you stupid slag!

1078
01:18:33,084 --> 01:18:35,753
<i>I can't tell if Miho is alive or dead,</i>

1079
01:18:35,836 --> 01:18:40,758
<i>but I'm on my feet and every ounce
of me wants to get some killing done.</i>

1080
01:18:43,511 --> 01:18:48,015
You want the head now, sweetheart?
So come down and get it!

1081
01:18:52,770 --> 01:18:54,772
Brave lad.

1082
01:18:54,855 --> 01:18:58,943
I could've put a bullet
straight down your ear just now,

1083
01:18:59,026 --> 01:19:02,863
if I hadn't got me revolver
all wet and useless.

1084
01:19:02,947 --> 01:19:06,826
You got the drop on me, love.
I'm as helpless as a baby.

1085
01:19:14,667 --> 01:19:17,628
I got to come clean
with you, sweetheart.

1086
01:19:17,711 --> 01:19:22,716
It was an outright lie I was giving ya
about me revolver being wet.

1087
01:19:22,800 --> 01:19:25,428
You see, I'm not
too fond of shootin'.

1088
01:19:25,511 --> 01:19:28,597
It's my preference to blow things up.

1089
01:19:28,681 --> 01:19:30,808
Once you blast the roof off a pub

1090
01:19:30,891 --> 01:19:34,895
and seen all the parts
flying off people,

1091
01:19:34,979 --> 01:19:38,149
a little bang bang's
never gonna match the sight of that.

1092
01:19:38,983 --> 01:19:44,488
Here's me, with all these fine grenades
and such a sweet beauty of a remote.

1093
01:19:44,572 --> 01:19:48,117
But it's me knife
I'll be doing you with.

1094
01:19:48,200 --> 01:19:50,786
You killed me mates.

1095
01:19:50,870 --> 01:19:55,332
Someone shoulda told ya: never give
an Irishman good cause for revenge.

1096
01:19:57,293 --> 01:19:59,462
<i>Deadly little Miho.</i>

1097
01:20:00,254 --> 01:20:03,048
<i>You won't feel a thing
unless she wants you to.</i>

1098
01:20:03,132 --> 01:20:05,926
<i>She twists the blade.</i>

1099
01:20:06,385 --> 01:20:07,761
<i>He feels it.</i>

1100
01:20:10,598 --> 01:20:14,351
<i>I tell Miho what we're gonna do
and how we're gonna do it.</i>

1101
01:20:14,435 --> 01:20:18,939
<i>I grab poor Dallas's car phone and make
the most important call of my life.</i>

1102
01:20:19,023 --> 01:20:23,986
<i>First, we gotta rescue Gail,
then comes the kill.</i>

1103
01:20:24,069 --> 01:20:28,032
<i>The big, fat kill.</i>

1104
01:20:38,334 --> 01:20:41,212
Do we just gotta stand here
and watch this?

1105
01:20:41,295 --> 01:20:43,130
What, are you kidding me, man?

1106
01:20:43,214 --> 01:20:46,884
I could watch old Manute do his thing
all night and not get tired of it.

1107
01:20:46,967 --> 01:20:48,469
I mean, the man's an artist.

1108
01:20:48,552 --> 01:20:53,641
Only an artist should be allowed
to touch such a beautiful subject.

1109
01:20:53,724 --> 01:20:55,684
Your skin is perfect.

1110
01:20:55,768 --> 01:20:58,896
Your nerves, responsive.

1111
01:20:58,979 --> 01:21:00,314
Beautiful.

1112
01:21:00,397 --> 01:21:03,484
Just give them what they want, Gail.

1113
01:21:07,530 --> 01:21:10,616
- Becky?
- It's over, Gail.

1114
01:21:11,283 --> 01:21:14,995
There's no fighting them.
Dwight's dead.

1115
01:21:15,079 --> 01:21:17,331
They got what's left
of that cop we killed.

1116
01:21:17,414 --> 01:21:20,501
Mob's gonna turn it over to the chief,
cops'll mow us down.

1117
01:21:20,584 --> 01:21:22,419
We gotta cut a deal.

1118
01:21:22,503 --> 01:21:26,090
You little bitch! You sold us out!

1119
01:21:26,173 --> 01:21:29,176
I didn't have no choice!
They was gonna hurt my mom.

1120
01:21:29,260 --> 01:21:33,430
You gotta cut a deal with these people.
It's selfish, you holding out like this.

1121
01:21:33,514 --> 01:21:36,350
You'll get a lot of girls killed
for no good reason.

1122
01:21:36,433 --> 01:21:38,936
It wasn't your mom!

1123
01:21:39,019 --> 01:21:42,147
We could have protected her
and you know it.

1124
01:21:42,231 --> 01:21:44,942
It was the money,
you stupid little bitch!

1125
01:21:45,025 --> 01:21:48,862
Sure, there's money. Sure, you
could've moved my mom into Old Town

1126
01:21:48,946 --> 01:21:51,740
and let her know
that her daughter's a goddamn whore.

1127
01:21:51,824 --> 01:21:53,951
Breaks your heart, doesn't it?

1128
01:21:54,034 --> 01:21:58,789
They offered me what you couldn't
never offer me: a way out.

1129
01:21:58,872 --> 01:22:00,749
I had to watch out for my own neck.

1130
01:22:00,833 --> 01:22:02,459
Your neck.

1131
01:22:02,543 --> 01:22:06,839
Your precious, scrawny, little neck!

1132
01:22:10,926 --> 01:22:15,014
You're crazy! You could have
ripped my throat out, you crazy whore!

1133
01:22:16,557 --> 01:22:20,060
Schutz, fetch my blades.

1134
01:22:20,144 --> 01:22:24,064
- Stuka, kill this one.
- No, I was promised!

1135
01:22:24,148 --> 01:22:26,984
Stupid little bitch!
You deserve worse!

1136
01:22:27,067 --> 01:22:30,613
I knew there was a reason
I got out of bed this morning.

1137
01:22:32,573 --> 01:22:34,617
Hey.

1138
