01:53:58,832 --> 01:54:03,795
<i>After a while, all I'm doing is pounding
wet chunks of bone into the floorboards,</i>

1586
01:54:03,879 --> 01:54:05,088
<i>so I stop.</i>

1587
01:54:06,631 --> 01:54:09,092
So long, Junior.

1588
01:54:09,176 --> 01:54:11,720
Been a pleasure.

1589
01:54:17,100 --> 01:54:20,604
I didn't scream, Hartigan, not once.

1590
01:54:22,022 --> 01:54:25,817
- I didn't scream.
- I know it, baby.

1591
01:54:25,901 --> 01:54:28,236
You grew up strong.

1592
01:54:39,748 --> 01:54:43,126
<i>By the time I get her to the car,
Nancy stops shaking.</i>

1593
01:54:43,210 --> 01:54:47,130
<i>Her skin is warm again.
She's herself again.</i>

1594
01:54:47,214 --> 01:54:49,674
Thanks for remembering my coat.

1595
01:54:51,009 --> 01:54:52,969
And for all the little things.

1596
01:54:53,053 --> 01:54:57,140
Like saving my life, twice.

1597
01:54:58,266 --> 01:55:01,353
- You better get rolling.
- You're not coming along?

1598
01:55:01,436 --> 01:55:06,399
No. I have friends on their way,
to collect evidence.

1599
01:55:06,483 --> 01:55:09,194
I'm gonna blow
this whole sick mess wide open.

1600
01:55:09,277 --> 01:55:11,613
I'm gonna clear my name.

1601
01:55:11,696 --> 01:55:15,742
I'm gonna put Senator Roark
behind bars where he belongs.

1602
01:55:15,826 --> 01:55:19,371
I can't lose you, not again.

1603
01:55:21,832 --> 01:55:24,709
You'll never lose me, Nancy.

1604
01:55:37,597 --> 01:55:41,393
<i>Nancy Callahan, the love of my life.</i>

1605
01:55:42,769 --> 01:55:47,274
<i>Shame to lie to her.
I hope she forgives me for it.</i>

1606
01:55:47,357 --> 01:55:50,944
<i>Get Senator Roark behind bars? Sure.</i>

1607
01:55:51,027 --> 01:55:54,573
<i>Maybe after I've pulled off that
miracle, I'll go and punch out God.</i>

1608
01:55:54,656 --> 01:55:58,451
<i>There isn't a prosecutor in the state
who'll go after Senator Roark.</i>

1609
01:55:58,535 --> 01:56:00,704
<i>I killed his only son.</i>

1610
01:56:00,787 --> 01:56:02,873
<i>The bloodline is cut.</i>

1611
01:56:02,956 --> 01:56:05,792
<i>Roark's lost his goddamn legacy.</i>

1612
01:56:05,959 --> 01:56:08,670
<i>He'll use all his power
to get revenge on me.</i>

1613
01:56:08,753 --> 01:56:12,132
<i>He'll go after me through Nancy.
He'll find her again.</i>

1614
01:56:12,215 --> 01:56:14,885
<i>There'll be no end to it.</i>

1615
01:56:14,968 --> 01:56:17,012
<i>She'll never be safe.</i>

1616
01:56:17,095 --> 01:56:19,848
<i>Not as long as I'm alive.</i>

1617
01:56:19,931 --> 01:56:22,517
<i>There's only one way to beat him.</i>

1618
01:56:23,143 --> 01:56:25,812
<i>An old man dies,</i>

1619
01:56:25,896 --> 01:56:28,148
<i>a young woman lives.</i>

1620
01:56:29,232 --> 01:56:31,484
<i>Fair trade.</i>

1621
01:56:34,446 --> 01:56:37,365
<i>I love you, Nancy.</i>

1622
01:56:44,331 --> 01:56:46,416
Yes.

1623
01:56:46,499 --> 01:56:48,668
Oh, Mom, don't go on like that.

1624
01:56:48,752 --> 01:56:54,090
It's not the city. I could've gotten
in a traffic accident anywhere.

1625
01:56:54,174 --> 01:56:57,761
Yeah, just a fracture.
The doctor said it's a clean break.

1626
01:56:57,844 --> 01:57:00,096
It should be right as rain in no time.

1627
01:57:19,324 --> 01:57:22,619
<i>Turn the right corner in Sin City</i>

1628
01:57:22,702 --> 01:57:27,374
<i>and you can find... anything.</i>

1629
01:57:27,457 --> 01:57:29,167
Becky.

1630
01:57:31,086 --> 01:57:33,672
Care for a smoke?

1631
01:57:35,966 --> 01:57:38,218
Love you, too, Mom.

1632
01:57:40,220 --> 01:57:42,472
<i>Anything.</i>
